  "prompt": "What does a flashing folder with question mark mean on a Macbook?",
  "response": "On a MacBook, a flashing folder with a question mark typically indicates that your Mac is having trouble finding a bootable operating system. This can happen for several reasons:\n\n1. No operating system is installed\n2. The startup disk is damaged or erased\n3. The hard drive is disconnected or failing\n4. Operating system files are corrupted\n\nTo resolve this issue, you can try:\n- Restarting the computer\n- Holding Command + R during startup to enter Recovery Mode\n- Checking your hard drive using Disk Utility\n- Reinstalling macOS\n- Recovering from a backup\n\nIf these steps don't work, you may need professional technical support to diagnose and fix the problem.",
